## Why ID Naming Matters

IDs are critical for:
- **Debugging** - Easy identification in browser DevTools
- **JavaScript targeting** - Stimulus controllers, vanilla JS selectors
- **Accessibility** - Form label associations, ARIA references
- **Deep linking** - Anchor links within pages
- **Testing** - Reliable selectors in system tests
- **Team collaboration** - Self-documenting code

### The Problem with Poor ID Naming

```html
<!-- Bad: Cryptic, debugging nightmare -->
<div id="d1">
  <div id="d2">
    <form id="f1">
      <input id="i1">
      <button id="b1">Submit</button>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Good: Self-documenting, easy to debug -->
<div id="user-profile-container">
  <div id="user-profile-header">
    <form id="user-settings-form">
      <input id="user-email-input">
      <button id="user-settings-save-button">Submit</button>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>
```

**In Browser DevTools:**
- Cryptic IDs: "What is `d1`? What does `b1` do?"
- Clear IDs: "Oh, it's the user profile container with a settings form"

